      <p>
          For each of the following, classify the sampling technique described as <em>Simple Random Sample</em>, <em>Stratified Random Sampling</em>, <em>Cluster Sampling</em> or <em>Multi-Stage Sampling</em>.  Be sure to justify your choices.
          <ol>
              <li>To measure the effects of a sewage malfunction in a town, city randomly choses homes to have their water tested.</li>
              <li>To measure student satisfaction, students are grouped by major, and each students are randomly selected from each major to be surveyed.</li>
              <li>To measure the cost of living in a city, a few grocery stores are randomly selected, and their prices analyzed.</li>
              <li>To measure customer satisfaction, a store randomly selects a few days and surveys the shoppers on those days.</li>
              <li>To measure potential allergic reactions to a medication, random users of the medication are selected to be given tested.</li>
              <li>To measure the cost of living in a city, the city is divided into square mile regions, and a few of these regions are randomly selected, and all the grocery stores within them have their prices analyzed.</li>
          </ol>
          
